    "description": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">When you select this archetype at 1st level, you gain a boon of draconic power.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Choose a damage type as your draconic damage type: fire, cold, lightning, acid, or poison.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>Once chosen this cannot be changed.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">Select one of the following:</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\"><strong><s>Dragon Curse</s></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\"><strong>Draconic Breath</strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">You may use an action to breath out a 15 foot cone or 5 foot wide 30 long foot line.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>You choose the shape of this breath when you gain this ability and cannot change it. Creatures in the area must make a Dexterity saving throw against your warlock spell save DC or take 2d6 damage of your draconic damage type on a failure or half damage on a success. If your draconic damage type is cold or poison, they must instead make a Constitution saving throw.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">This damage increases by 1d6 at 10th level, and again at 15th and 20th level.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">At 14th level the area increases to a 30 foot cone or a 5 foot wide, 60 foot long line.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">You can use this attack a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus and regain all expended uses when you finish a short or long rest.</p>",
